 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of root things which enable a common approach to identification and provenance to be defined for all things within an application domain.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>a root entity from which all other entities within a domain inherit;</li>
   <li>a global identifier an entity;</li>
   <li>the activity of creating a record of an entity;</li>
   <li>the definition of an information object as a set of statements.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>the different types of entity necessary for recording the information within a domain.</li>
 </outscope>



